						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is in characters of the sixth-century A.D. It is stated to be erected in memory of a hero who died in a cattle raid. It appears that a certain Māndhatri[varman] was the overlord and a Vaidumba king (name lost) was governing the area around the village Mōdugalapalle.</p>						

						</summary>
